FBIS4-46122 "jptot022__l94031" JPRS-TOT-94-022-L JPRS Terrorism FOUO 21 May 1994 NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA REGIONAL AFFAIRS IDF Seizes `Terrorist' Leader al-Dirani; Hizballah Reaction IDF Seizes `Terrorist' Leader al-Dirani; Hizballah Reaction Corroborating Information Sought on Arad TA2105083094 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 0700 GMT 21 May 94 TA2105083094 Tel Aviv IDF Radio Hebrew BFN [Report by political correspondent Udi Segal] [Excerpt] [passage omitted] A senior political source said that if al-Dirani's interrogation corroborated the information Israel already possessed according to which Ron Arad had been turned over to the Revolutionary Guards, Iran would no longer be able to deny any connection to this affair. Approximately one month ago, in the framework of a conference in Bucharest, I asked Iranian Foreign Minister 'Ali Akbar Velayati why Iran continued to hold navigator Ron Arad prisoner? [Begin recording] Segal, in English: Why is your country, Iran, still holding the Israeli POW Ron Arad? Velayati, in English: I do not know how much this is related to the present discussion that we have, but I categorically deny that there is any prisoner from Israel in Iran. [passage omitted]
